---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About — Fabric Planning"
  description="About Khaled Chowdhury, the Fabric Whisperer, and Data Crafters — the team behind the Fabric Planning knowledge hub."
>
  {/* ============================================================ */}
  {/* Hero */}
  {/* ============================================================ */}
  <section
    class="relative w-full text-white"
    style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f2b1e 0%, #1a1035 50%, #0f2b1e 100%);"
  >
    <div
      class="mx-auto flex max-w-[1200px] flex-col items-center px-6 py-20 text-center md:py-28"
    >
      <p
        class="mb-6 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-light-purple"
      >
        About
      </p>
      <h1
        class="mb-6 max-w-3xl text-4xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight text-white md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl"
      >
        Built by practitioners, for practitioners
      </h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ============================================================ */}
  {/* Section 1: The Fabric Whisperer */}
  {/* ============================================================ */}
  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1200px] px-6 py-20 md:py-24">
      <div class="grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-[280px_1fr]">
        <div>
          <img
            src="https://media.fabricplanning.io/branding/Khaled%20Chowdhury%20Headshot.JPG"
            alt="Headshot of Khaled Chowdhury, the Fabric Whisperer"
            class="aspect-square w-full rounded-xl object-cover"
          />
        </div>

        <div>
          <p
            class="mb-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-fabric-purple"
          >
            The Fabric Whisperer
          </p>
          <h2
            class="mb-2 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-forest md:text-4xl"
          >
            Khaled Chowdhury
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-lg text-gray-muted">
            The Fabric Whisperer | CEO &amp; Co-Founder, Data Crafters
          </p>
          <p class="mb-8 text-sm font-medium text-slate-text">
            CMA &nbsp;|&nbsp; FPAC &nbsp;|&nbsp; Certified Chief Data Officer
            (Carnegie Mellon) &nbsp;|&nbsp; Top 50 Data Analytics Professional
            (2023)
          </p>

          <div class="space-y-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-text md:text-lg">
            <p>
              I spent over 15 years in FP&amp;A, living inside Excel, building
              budget models, and managing planning cycles at companies like
              Momentive, KMG, and CMC Materials. I know what it feels like to
              spend three months on a budget cycle, wrestling with broken
              links, version control nightmares, and the constant question of
              whether the numbers are right.
            </p>
            <p>
              When I founded Data Crafters, I brought that finance perspective
              into the Microsoft Fabric ecosystem. We became a Microsoft Fabric
              Featured Partner, and I started leading the Houston Fabric User
              Group. But it was always the planning side that excited me most,
              because I knew firsthand how broken the process was for most
              mid-market companies.
            </p>
            <p>
              When Microsoft announced Fabric Planning at FabCon 2026, I saw
              something I had been waiting for: a native planning capability
              built directly into the platform where the data already lives.
              No more duct-taping external tools to Power BI. No more
              uncertified custom visuals. No more paying for 200 licenses when
              only 50 people are actively planning.
            </p>
            <p>
              That&rsquo;s why I built Fabric Planning (the website). This is
              not a sales pitch. This is a knowledge hub for finance and data
              professionals who want to understand what Fabric Planning can
              actually do, where the gaps are, and how to get started. I&rsquo;ve
              been in your shoes. I&rsquo;m building this because it&rsquo;s
              what I wish existed when I was evaluating tools from the other
              side of the table.
            </p>
            <p class="text-slate-text/80">
              Use things. Love people. Worship the divine.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-8">
            <a
              href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/khaledchowdhury/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg border border-dc-blue px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-dc-blue hover:bg-dc-blue hover:text-white"
            >
              Connect on LinkedIn &rarr;
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ============================================================ */}
  {/* Section 2: Collaborators */}
  {/* ============================================================ */}
  <section class="bg-purple-wash">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1200px] px-6 py-20 md:py-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-center">
        <h2
          class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-forest md:text-4xl"
        >
          Collaborators
        </h2>
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-text md:text-lg">
          Fabric Planning is a collaborative effort. We&rsquo;re building a
          community of practitioners, thought leaders, and community builders
          who are passionate about Microsoft Fabric Planning. More
          collaborators coming soon.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ============================================================ */}
  {/* Section 3: Sponsored by Data Crafters */}
  {/* ============================================================ */}
  <section class="bg-forest text-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1200px] px-6 py-20 md:py-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <p
          class="mb-4 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-mint-teal"
        >
          Sponsor
        </p>
        <h2
          class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white md:text-4xl"
        >
          Sponsored by Data Crafters
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-10 text-base leading-relaxed text-white/85 md:text-lg">
          Data Crafters is a Microsoft Fabric Featured Partner consultancy
          serving mid-market companies across the United States. As a
          Solutions Partner for Data &amp; AI and Digital &amp; App Innovation
          with an Analytics on Azure specialization, Data Crafters helps
          organizations build their data foundation on Microsoft Fabric.
          Fabric Planning is an independent knowledge hub sponsored by Data
          Crafters. The content is community-driven and vendor-neutral.
        </p>
        <a
          href="https://datacrafters.io"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg px-8 py-4 text-base font-semibold text-white shadow-md transition hover:shadow-lg"
          style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #3BA776 0%, #1B7A50 100%);"
        >
          Visit datacrafters.io &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
